Privacy Policy (English)
Privacy Policy
Your privacy is very important to us. For this reason, all employees of Fun Flavor Games Martin Dirks ("FFG", "we" or "our")
    agreed to protect your ("user" or "you") personal rights.
The following privacy policy ("Policies") points out how we collect, store, use and manage the personal information you provide us or is collected on our websites. Including, but not limited to,
    www.funflavorgames.com, www.funflavorgames.de, www.hero-park.com, www.hero-park.de or any FFG game available on mobile platforms, including iOS and Android ("service"). The scope of this Policy
    is limited to information that were collected or obtained by FFG through your use of the Service. We are not responsible for the actions of third parties or companies.
By using the Service, you agree to the terms of this Policy, including the processing of your data and personal information. If you do not agree with the conditions described in this policy, do
    not use the service.
Please contact info@funflavorgames.com if you have any questions or concerns about this policy.
Responsible in the sense of the data protection regulation and other national data protection laws of the European Union as well as other data protection regulations is:
Fun Flavor Games
Martin Dirks
Wilhelmstraße 35
58706 Menden
Germany
Phone:+491797556339
E-Mail: info@funflavorgames.com
Collection and use of information
The following describes how FFG collects information on different platforms.
The
    main objective of FFG to collect and use information is to provide you with services, create your account, contact you, improve the service and generate reports for internal use.
We may store this information on our servers or servers of our affiliates.
Websites of  FFG
When you browse FFG's websites, your computer's IP address (Internet Protocol), operating system, access times,
    browser type and language and referring website addresses may be automatically logged.
This information may be used to collectively analyze the use of the Service.
We may ask you for personal information, including but not limited to your name, background, gender, age, or email address, to conduct research, display ads, and analyze
    reports for internal user trends.
We may use your e-mail address to ask for feedback about our services or to notify you of updates and upcoming promotions.
Please contact info@funflavorgames.com if you no longer wish to receive these emails.
You can also opt out by following the unsubscribe link
    at the end of each communication.
Social media
Our service may use social media features, including the Facebook Like button and the Twitter Follow button and
    related widgets.
These features and widgets are either hosted directly in our service or by third parties.
They can track your IP address, the service
    you are currently using, and set a cookie for the feature to work properly.
They are subject to the privacy policies of the particular company providing
    them.
Customer service
When you contact our customer service, we collect your e-mail address to communicate with you.
We may also use your email address to request feedback on our services or to notify you of updates and upcoming promotions.
Please contact
    info@funflavorgames.com if you no longer wish to receive these emails.
You can also opt out by following the unsubscribe link at the end of each
    communication.
Mobile
platforms
Using our games on a mobile platform, including but not limited to iOS and Android, allows us to record and store information
    such as your unique device ID, the International Mobile Device Identity (IMEI), the Media Access Control (MAC) address , hardware type, your device name, the version of your operating system
    ("operating system"), your e-mail address (if you have used Facebook or Google as your login) and your location (based on your IP address). We use this information to analyze user trends and
    troubleshooting. Your IP-based location (country-specific) will be used to provide you with the right service and give you the ability to interact with other players in your environment. We will
    not share this information with third parties without your permission. We'll also create a unique user ID that will be stored and linked to your information to track your use of our
    games.
Game
data collection
FFG collects data about your interactions with our game and other players.
This
    information is collected and linked to your Player ID, IP address or Device ID to improve our service.
Login services
You can log in to our service using login services ("SN service") such as Game Center, Facebook Login and Google Signup to
    verify your identity and give you the ability to provide certain personal information, such as your name or email address to us. For example, Facebook signup lets you post your most recent
    activity to our services on your social network. FFG can use the SN service to collect and record information in accordance with the policies and conditions of the relevant SN service. These may
    include: (1) your name, (2) your SN service user identification number and / or username, (3) locale, city, state and country, (4) gender, (5) date of birth, (6) email address, (7) profile
    picture or its URL and (8) the SN service user identification numbers of your friends who are also connected to FFG games. Please contact info@funflavorgames.com if you wish to delete your data
    received from SN Services. FFG can also offer you to invite your contacts from a SN service. That way, your contacts can be found in FFG games so you can invite them to FFG games. We can use this
    information to send invitations to these contacts. Contact info@funflavorgames.com if you would like related information removed from our database.
Notifications
From time to time, we'll send you push notifications about our mobile applications to let you know about game
    updates, customer feedback, and other notifications.
You can opt out of this service at any time by disabling push notifications in the device
    settings.
Other collection
We may also receive information from your participation in (1) surveys, (2) contests or (3) competitions about
    the service.
If you voluntarily choose to participate in surveys, contests or competitions, we may request certain personal information from you, which may include contact
    information (such as name and address) and demographic information (such as postal code).
This information may be used to improve our games or to engage with raffle
    winners.
Tracking technologies and third-party services
We, partners, or analytics service providers use technologies such as cookies, scripts, and tags to identify a user's computer
    or device and to track and store information about their visit, such as their preferences or username and password. This information may be linked to your personal information, such as your user
    ID. This is done to improve the quality of our services, to tailor recommendations to your interests and to facilitate the use of the service. Cookies can be disabled at any time, but you may
    lose access to certain features of the service.
Our services may include third-party tracking tools from our service providers. Examples include Google Firebase and Unity Analytics. These third parties may use cookies, SDKs and APIs in our
    services to collect and analyze user information, including information such as device ID, MAC address, IMEI, geo-location information (country specific) and IP address to provide their services
    under their respective Privacy Policy. We use mobile analytics software to better understand the functionality of our mobile software on your device. This software may record information such as:
    For example, how often you use the application, what events occur in the application, performance data, aggregated usage, and where the application was downloaded. We do not associate the
    information we store in the analytics software with personal information that you submit in the mobile application.
All third-party services have access to individual data only if they are required to fulfill their duties and if FFG is required to provide its service. All providers have been notified of this
    privacy policy and are acting in strict accordance with their own privacy policy and legal framework. Information and information on individually transmitted data can be requested at any time,
    provided the information is due in accordance with German data protection law and disclosure does not violate the privacy of third parties or a legitimate business interest. Because we have no
    access to or control over third parties, our Privacy Policy does not cover the use of third-party tools. We are not responsible for third-party data collection practices and we recommend that you
    read the privacy policy to learn more about the use of cookies and other technologies. Below is a list of partners within the service, including information about their privacy policy:
Unity Analytics: https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
Google Firebase: https://firebase.google.com/terms
Google Analytics: http://www.google.com.au/analytics/learn/privacy.html
Apple: https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/
